result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Katie J. Honzik in court with attorney Paul M Goetz.  Jill Laufenberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF223 and 15CM35 @ 3:16 p.m. Agreement stated - 15CM35 State moves to dismiss and read in. 15CF223 - Def will waive prelim hrg, Def will plead to cts 1, 3, 5, & 8, all other cts dismiss and read in. Ct 1 - defer judgment 2 yrs, written agreement. Cts 3 & 5 - withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, any other counseling deemed necessary, court costs.  Ct 8 - withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation AODA and follow through, costs, State will argue for 90 days jail or stipulate to 60 days. Atty Goetz agrees, Def will stipulate to 60 days. 24 days credit if revoked. Def agrees. Court reviews preliminary hrg rights. Court accepts waiver as knowing and voluntary, finds probable cause and binds over. Information filed. Copy received, reading waived. Plea quest. reviewed. Ct 1 - no contest plea. Ct 3 - no contest plea. Ct 5 - no contest plea. Ct 8 - no contest. Court grants motion to dismiss 15CM35, to be read in, 15CF223 dismiss and read in cts 2, 4, 6 & 7. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Goetz satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas. Court approves deferred entry of judgment on ct 1, reviews terms of written agreement with Def. Court finds guilty of ct 3,  ct 5, ct 8. Sentencing remarks by Atty Goetz. Response by State. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Court will follow agreement. Ct 3 -sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, any other counseling deemed appropriate, court costs. Apply bond to all costs. DNA sample and surcharge. (DNA surcharge on all 3 cts) Ct 5 - sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, same conditions, costs, concurrent with ct 3. Credit for 24 days served if revoked on cts 3, 5, & 8. Ct 8 - withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, same conditions and concurrent, costs, 60 days jail, huber if eligible. Report no later than 6 p.m. on 4/15/16.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights. Court will set $500 signature bond on ct 1.  Review hearing scheduled for February 20, 2018 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Katie J. Honzik in court, in custody & via-video with attorney Paul M Goetz.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls 15CF223 & 15CM35  @ 2:23 pm.  15CF223 Atty Goetz has copy of complaint, waives reading, Def. advised of charges & penalties.  Court goes over charges & penalties. Atty Goetz gives bond arguments. State gives bond arguments. Def. must reside with parents. No contact with A.H, no possession drugs without valid prescriptions and take as prescribed.  Def. would like to go to treatment. Court will reduce bond to $500.00 cash bond with conditions.  Atty Goetz waives time limits. Def. agrees to waive time limits. Court accepts waiver & will reserve right to have later date. Atty Goetz can appear by phone.  Def. does not have to appear.  Status conference scheduled for February 1, 2016 at 03:30 pm.

Defendant Katie J. Honzik in court with attorney Gary Stephen Dodge.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Not guilty plea entered.  Court will accept not gulty plea.  Bond will continue  Status conference scheduled for June 1, 2015 at 03:30 pm.
No possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription.

Defendant Katie J. Honzik in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Def has copy of complaint.  Court reads charge with possible penalties.  Def advised of right to an atty.  State request signature bond with condition.  Bond set by court.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for April 27, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
